	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65198971"><p>I ran into this formula 30 years ago, and it still works</p><p>"Take your developers best estimate, add 40% to it, then double it"</p><p>The 40% represents test cases that the developer did not consider and doubling it handles the need to rework the entire assembly</p><p>Some would call it sandbagging, but it has helped me many times over the past 3 decades</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65198971">

